data.persona: I lurk beyond the city walls and wait for any hapless traveler to wander by. My fangs are sharp and my claws are always ready. I lie ready to taste human blood again.
data.description:
You are in the Bog.
Frogs croak in the reeds that surround the bog. The water is very murky and underneath the surface tadpoles dart around. There are minimal places to stand to stay dry.
There's a water, a reeds, a bog, a moss, and a tree here.
The turtles and the lizards are here.

You are carrying nothing.
